"## CrossCheck review — staged (1 file, +3 / −0)

_Generated 1970-01-01 00:00 UTC · CrossCheck v0.0.0-test · heuristic (offline) mode_

### Risk map

| Severity | Cluster | Files | Lines |
|---|---|---|---|
| ▲ HIGH | db: drop_sessions migration | 1 | +3 / −0 |

### Review checklist

- [ ] **(HIGH)** Read the migration line by line — do not skim migrations, ever — \`migrations/0007_drop_sessions.sql:1\`
- [ ] **(HIGH)** Confirm every DROP/TRUNCATE targets something truly disposable (not renamed-away production data) — \`migrations/0007_drop_sessions.sql:1\`
- [ ] **(HIGH)** For NOT NULL columns without DEFAULT: confirm the backfill strategy and table-lock impact — \`migrations/0007_drop_sessions.sql:1\`
- [ ] **(HIGH)** Write or verify the DOWN/rollback migration before pushing — \`migrations/0007_drop_sessions.sql:1\`
- [ ] **(MED)** Run the migration against a production-shaped dump locally; confirm backfill + rollback path — \`migrations/0007_drop_sessions.sql:1\`
- [ ] **(MED)** Confirm the migration is reversible — a DOWN path exists and actually runs — \`migrations/0007_drop_sessions.sql:1\`
- [ ] **(MED)** Check lock impact: table rewrites and index builds on large tables need a plan — \`migrations/0007_drop_sessions.sql:1\`
- [ ] **(MED)** Confirm app code and schema land together (no deploy order that strands either side) — \`migrations/0007_drop_sessions.sql:1\`
- [ ] **(GENERAL)** Read the full diff of every ▲ cluster top to bottom — rules catch patterns, not logic

### Manual tests performed

- [ ] Restore a production-shaped dump locally and run the migration against it
- [ ] Run the down migration and confirm the app still boots
- [ ] Run the app against the migrated schema and exercise the affected feature end to end
- [ ] Apply the migration to a copy of production-shaped data and boot the app against it

> Heuristics catch patterns, not logic. This report records that a human
> reviewed the change; it is not a guarantee of correctness."
`;

